verbose_text: Many individuals with TDSD and a minority with OTDSD have a translocation of the testis determining SRY gene, usually onto one of the X chromosomes, whereas a small proportion have chromosomal rearrangements associated with upregulation (gain-of-function) of SOX gene expression (e.g., duplications of the RevSex [MIM : 616425] enhancer of SOX9 [MIM : 608160] and rearrangements of the SOX3 locus [MIM : 800833]).
